Unnamed: 1: User specified price shocks - by food item group and rural and urban areas.
Price shocks should not exceed either +50% or -50% to maintain model plausibility. Any shocks specified should be understood as relative to nonfood prices (see User Guide).

Unnamed: 7:
Food price shocks are entered here. 

To enter the shocks, simply type the desired percentage change, either positive or negative, in the specified cell. 

In the example below, we have typed "5" and "-5" to increase rural rice prices by 5% and decrease urban maize prices by "5%"
